 different polarizations would be quite possible\ndue to their very high frequencies, large energy densities and special\nproperties of spectrum. (iv)Detection band(10^8 to 10^12 Hz or higher) of PPFs\nby 3DSR and observation range(7*10^7 to 3*10^9 Hz) of PPFs by FAST\n(Five-hundred-meter-Aperture-Spherical Telescope, China), have a certain\noverlapping property, so their coincidence experiments will have high\ncomplementarity.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 3 Dec 2017 13:24:39 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 23 Dec 2017 08:22:13 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 3 May 2018 11:36:19 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Mon, 26 Nov 2018 15:41:56 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Thu, 29 Nov 2018 13:56:48 GMT"},{"version":"v6","created":"Wed, 23 Jun 2021 16:55:55 GMT"},{"version":"v7","created":"Wed, 22 Dec 2021 02:53:46 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-12-23"}
